add forward test: fails on stateful classes' attributes

The caller is now accessed twice, but if the owner of the called attribute is stateful and changes on each access, then this can fail the test. This test checks that. Right now, it fails.

add forward_transitive decorator

This mainly affects the expected keywords check: using the new decorator, makes sure that, inside decorated functions, the expected keywords from nested calls to other kwandl forwarded are also taken into account for the top-level decorated call. This works recursively.

One corner case still doesn't work; a currently failing test case was added for that.

fix final transitivity test case

To do so, I added the original function's name as an attribute to the decorator wrapped function so that that can be used as a key to the global table instead. This name will be accessible to new references to the object as well, so the actual function name doesn't matter anymore.
